name: Surskit
flavorText: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Masquerain
flavorText: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, shuffle an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their deck.

name: Froslass ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out, flip a coin. If heads, your opponent takes 1 fewer Prize card.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Pansage
flavorText: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Simisage
flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
Ability1Text: If you have Simisage, Simisear, and Simipour in play, ignore all Colorless Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Pokemon that have an Ability, except any Simisage.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

name: Crustle
flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks from Evolution Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled- down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Steenee
flavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Blipbug
flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokemon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dottler
flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Orbeetle
flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your opponent's discard pile.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Nymble
flavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it's in a tough spot, this Pokemon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Nymble
flavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it's in a tough spot, this Pokemon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Toedscruel
flavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.
Ability1Text: Cards in your opponent's discard pile can't be put into their hand by an effect of your opponent's Abilities or Trainer cards.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Wo-Chien
flavorText: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Grass Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokemon cost ColorlessColorless more.

name: Magby
flavorText: This Pokemon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.

name: Pansear
flavorText: This Pokemon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Simisear
flavorText: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
Ability1Text: If you have Simisage, Simisear, and Simipour in play, ignore all Colorless Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Attack1Text: Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokemon and attach a Basic Fire Energy card from your discard pile to each of them.

name: Fuecoco
flavorText: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

name: Crocalor
flavorText: The combination of Crocalor's fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokemon's head.
Attack1Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokemon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokemon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Armarouge ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has full HP, it takes 80 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Iron Moth
flavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokemon's traits match up with an object described in an old book.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokemon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may move any amount of Fire Energy from your other Pokemon to it.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Heat Ray.

name: Chi-Yu
flavorText: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Horsea
flavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
flavorText: Seadra's mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Kingdra
flavorText: Scales shed by this Pokemon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they've been given to royalty as gifts.
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 6 cards of your deck. This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Energy card you find there. Then, discard those Energy cards and shuffle the other cards back into your deck. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Remoraid
flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokemon tries to use an attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Feebas
flavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokemon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Milotic
flavorText: It's said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may use this Ability. Each player puts a Basic Pokemon from their discard pile onto their Bench. (Your opponent puts a Basic Pokemon onto their Bench first.)
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Fighting Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Garchomp ex
Attack1Text: Attach up to 3 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Mantyke
flavorText: It swims along with a school of Remoraid, and they'll all fight together to repel attackers.
Attack1Text: Heal 120 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Palkia
flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Panpour
flavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Simipour
flavorText: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
Ability1Text: If you have Simisage, Simisear, and Simipour in play, ignore all Colorless Energy in the costs of attacks used by this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Vanillite
flavorText: Supposedly, this Pokemon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it's a kind Pokemon.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: People believe this Pokemon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: Your opponent's Pokemon that have 40 HP or less remaining can't attack.

name: Tsareena ex
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon until its remaining HP is 30.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon, and it recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy's presence.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy's presence.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Golisopod
flavorText: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner's meal.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

name: Golisopod ex
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokemon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokemon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Wugtrio
flavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Pokemon Tool cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Veluza
flavorText: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, move up to 2 Water Energy cards from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Dondozo
flavorText: This Pokemon is a glutton, but it's bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. You may attach any number of Basic Energy cards you find there to this Pokemon. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Iron Bundle
flavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokemon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokemon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokemon.) If you do, discard this Pokemon and all attached cards.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Chien-Pao
flavorText: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Mewtwo ex
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Psychic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Elekid
flavorText: It's not good at storing electricity yet. This Pokemon sneaks into people's homes, looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Plusle
flavorText: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Minun
flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
Ability1Text: If you have Plusle in play, whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon. The effect of Buddy Pulse doesn't stack.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Attack1Text: Choose Basic Lightning Energy cards from your discard pile up to the number of Prize cards your opponent has taken and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik latch on to other Pokemon and suck out static electricity. They're often found sticking to Yamper's hindquarters.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokemon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zekrom
flavorText: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 40 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Oricorio
flavorText: The energetic, cheerful dance of these Oricorio is popular with children, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a card for each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tapu Koko ex
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Toxel
flavorText: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokemon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Iron Hands ex
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 1 more Prize card.

name: Natu
flavorText: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Xatu
flavorText: This odd Pokemon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, draw 2 cards.

name: Latios
flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokemon that dislikes fighting.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Deoxys
flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokemon. It appears where auroras are seen.
Attack2Text: Move all Energy from this Pokemon to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Yamask
flavorText: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokemon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Cofagrigus ex
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Put 5 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Pumpkaboo
flavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokemon that see it.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Gourgeist
flavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, discard 2 random cards from your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Flittle
flavorText: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Flittle
flavorText: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Espathra
flavorText: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokemon done to this Pokemon until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack1Text: If Tulip is in your discard pile, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Tinkatink
flavorText: This Pokemon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it's satisfied with the result.
Attack1Text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may put that card into your hand. If you don't, discard that card and draw a card.

name: Tinkatink
flavorText: This Pokemon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it's satisfied with the result.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Tinkatuff
flavorText: These Pokemon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other's hammers by smashing them together.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Metal Energy attached, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Tinkaton
flavorText: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Metal Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Scream Tail
flavorText: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokemon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each damage counter on this Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Gimmighoul
flavorText: This Pokemon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gimmighoul
flavorText: This Pokemon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Iron Valiant ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokemon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Onix
flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Gligar
flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1.

name: Gliscor
flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1.

name: Groudon
flavorText: This legendary Pokemon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard up to 4 Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Gabite
flavorText: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: Though small, Mienfoo's temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokemon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: If you attached a Pokemon Tool card from your hand to this Pokemon during this turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Hoopa ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Bandit's Fist.

name: Minior
flavorText: This is its form when its shell has fallen off. The color of its core depends on the materials that made up the food it ate.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, when you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Toxtricity ex
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Lightning Energy from your Pokemon.

name: Nacli
flavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Nacli
flavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Naclstack
flavorText: This Pokemon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey's body.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Garganacl
flavorText: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokemon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, heal 30 damage from that Pokemon.

name: Klawf
flavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 160 more damage.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Flamigo
flavorText: This Pokemon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Slither Wing
flavorText: This mysterious Pokemon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 90 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Sandy Shocks ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if your opponent has 4 or fewer Prize cards remaining, you may attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Ting-Lu
flavorText: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has 4 or more damage counters on it, this attack does nothing.

name: Zubat
flavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun's light won't reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Golbat
flavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokemon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Crobat
flavorText: This Pokemon flaps its four wings skillfully. Crobat can fly through cramped caves without needing to slow down.
Attack1Text: Choose Item cards or Supporter cards. During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any of the chosen cards from their hand.

name: Absol
flavorText: Because of this Pokemon's ability to detect danger, people mistook Absol as a bringer of doom.
Attack1Text: You may discard any number of cards from your hand until you have 4 or fewer. Draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Liepard
flavorText: This stealthy Pokemon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
Attack1Text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokemon living in your room.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your hand. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Cunning and cautious, this Pokemon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Thievul
flavorText: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand, and then you choose 2 Energy cards you find there and shuffle them into your opponent's deck.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has no Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Move 2 Darkness Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Lokix
flavorText: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Brute Bonnet
flavorText: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokemon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon has an Ancient Booster Energy Capsule attached, you may make both Active Pokemon Poisoned.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Roaring Moon ex
Attack1Text: Knock Out your opponent's Active Pokemon. If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Knocked Out in this way, this Pokemon does 200 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: You may discard a Stadium in play. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Steelix
flavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage counters from being placed on your Benched Pokemon by effects of attacks used by your opponent's Basic Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed's spikes grow big and strong.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokemon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Spinning Needles attack does 100 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Durant
flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokemon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on all of your Durant.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Honedge
flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.

name: Honedge
flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Slicing Blade attack does 80 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokemon to build a kingdom to its liking.

name: Aegislash ex

name: Zacian
flavorText: Able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King's Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Metal Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Skeledirge ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard a Basic Fire Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. During this turn, attacks used by your Pokemon do 60 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Orthworm
flavorText: When attacked, this Pokemon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: If there are 3 or fewer cards in your deck, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Gholdengo ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw a card. If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, draw 1 more card.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Basic Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Altaria ex
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokemon done to this Pokemon. (Damage is not an effect.)

name: Tatsugiri
flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokemon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Porygon
flavorText: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokemon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon to 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the Pokemon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: Some say an additional program made this Pokemon evolve, but even academics can't agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, attach up to 4 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon. If tails, discard an Energy from this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Aipom
flavorText: It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Ambipom
flavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your hand.

name: Miltank
flavorText: This Pokemon needs to be milked every day, or else it will fall ill. The flavor of Miltank milk changes with the seasons.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was healed during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Whismur
flavorText: When Whismur cries, the sound of its own voice startles it, making the Pokemon cry even louder. It cries until it's exhausted, then it falls asleep.
Attack1Text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokemon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokemon.)

name: Loudred
flavorText: The force of this Pokemon's loud voice isn't just the sound—it's also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Exploud
flavorText: This Pokemon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind, it'll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.
Attack1Text: Discard your opponent's Active Pokemon and all attached cards. If this Pokemon didn't evolve from Loudred during this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Spinda
flavorText: Each Spinda's spot pattern is different. With its stumbling movements, it evades opponents' attacks brilliantly!
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Confused and is damaged by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Swablu
flavorText: It can't relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Tandemaus
flavorText: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Tandemaus

name: Cyclizar
flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Crustle
flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks from Evolution Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Fighting Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.
